            . I am a <rs id="t18240916-254-viclabel1359" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-254-victim2120 t18240916-254-viclabel1359"></join>, and live in Eastbourne-terrace. I had a jacket stolen from me the day before yesterday. I was at work under a gateway in <placeName id="t18240916-254-crimeloc1360">Sydney-street, Stepney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240916-254-crimeloc1360" type="placeName" value="Sydney-street, Stepney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240916-254-crimeloc1360" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-254-off1357 t18240916-254-crimeloc1360"></join>. I had gone out to an adjoining house, and on my return my jacket was gone. My handkerchief was in my hat, which was lying by the jacket. I received some information, and laid hold of the prisoner in an adjoining field; I charged him with stealing the jacket and handkerchief - he said he had done no such thing. I took him to the watchhouse. As soon as he saw me in the field, he dropped the articles, and went on. When I saw him first, he was rolling them up, and then ran away. I am quite sure he is the person. The field is about a quarter of a mile from the place where I was at work.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-254-person2122">
                  SARAH 
                  EVERETT
               <interp inst="t18240916-254-person2122" type="surname" value="EVERETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-254-person2122" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-254-person2122" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at Stepney. I saw the prisoner come out from the gateway with the jacket under his arm. I went to Pickett, and asked if he had lost a jacket. He came and said it was gone, and then pursued him.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming from one gang of bricklayers, and was going to another - this man was running, and he took hold of me, saying, I was the man. I said,</p>
               <p>"What do you want; I will go with you whereever you wish."</p>
